		<title>06WELSH IN PONTNEATHVAUGHAN.</title>
		<content> The children in Class 3 of the school 
 made a survey of the incidence of     
 Welsh speakers in their families.They 
 defined Welsh speakers as persons who 
 could carry on a conversation in      
 Welsh.We included all parents and     
 grandparents both living and dead.    
 We agreed that none of the children in
 this class was a Welsh speaker.       
 The figures were;                     
                                       
 Welsh speakers   -                    
                                       
 Parents 6(16.6%)  G/parents 26(36%)   
                                       
 Non Welsh speakers -                  
                                       
 Parents 30((83.3%) G/parents 46(64%)  
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       </content>
